また『延喜式』神名帳の編纂当時に存在したが同帳に記載の無い神社、いわゆる「[[延喜式神名帳|式外社]]」についても付記する。
-->

This is a '''List of Shikinaisha in Hizen Province'''. Or the list of shrines in [[Hizen Province]] which is present in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|qq=draft}}. On this page we will also cover the {{ill|Shikigeisha|ja|式外社|1=Shikigeisha|qq=draft}} of [[Hizen Province]] which are shrines that are known to have existed at that time due to other historical records, such as the [[Rikkokushi]], but for some reason were excluded from the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|qq=draft}}. We will cover them in a separate list to avoid confusion.
== Shikinai Shrines (式内社) == 『延喜式』神名帳では、大社1座1社（Myojin Taisha社）・小社3座3社の計4座4社を記載。
